-- Peru Stocks: Alturas, Atacocha, Maple, Minsur, Relapasa, Panoro
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-01-20T21:48:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/peru-stocks-alturas-atacocha-maple-minsur-relapasa-panoro.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  dropped for the first day this week,
falling 0.6 percent to 20,887.84. The  MSCI (MXPECAPD)  All Peru Capped Index
slid 0.4 percent to 2,679.43.  Mining shares slumped after metals declined in New York and
 London , said Janet Chong, a trader at Latinoamericana SAB.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, dropped 9.1 percent to 10 cents.  Cia.
Minera Atacocha SA (CMA\B)  (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc mining
company, fell 3.5 percent to 83 centimos.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1
PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin producer, declined 2.9
percent to 2.68 soles.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian
copper and gold exploration company, slid 1.7 percent to 57
cents.  Refiners dropped after crude fell for a third session in
New York.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, declined 1.7 percent to $1.18.
 Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, fell 1.1 percent to 90 centimos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
